# What I Learned Today

- O(1) = Constant Time
- O(n) = One Loop
- O(n²) = Two Nested Loops
- O(log n) = Divide by 2 Each Iteration
- Ignore Constants in Big O
- Keep the Dominant Term

# Quick Reference

| Pattern | Time Complexity |
|----------|------------|
| Access by index | O(1) |
| One loop | O(n) |
| Two nested loops | O(n²) |
| Three nested loops | O(n³) |
| Divide by 2 repeatedly | O(log n) |
| Loop + nested loop | O(n²) |
